_тЪая╕П Potential issue_ | _ЁЯЯа Major_

**Stop subscribing per-session streams to the shared channel.**

Both publishers now send session events to `agent:events` and `agent:events:${sessionId}`. Subscribing each SSE client to both and filtering only by `event.sessionId` means the owning client gets every session event twice, and every client still parses every other session's shared-channel traffic.



<details>
<summary>Suggested change</summary>

```diff
 async function subscribeToSession(sessionId: string, callback: (event: AgentEvent) => void): Promise<Redis> {
   const subscriber = new Redis(REDIS_URL);
-  await subscriber.subscribe(PUBSUB_CHANNEL, `${PUBSUB_CHANNEL}:${sessionId}`);
-  subscriber.on('message', (_channel: string, message: string) => {
+  const sessionChannel = `${PUBSUB_CHANNEL}:${sessionId}`;
+  await subscriber.subscribe(sessionChannel);
+  subscriber.on('message', (channel: string, message: string) => {
+    if (channel !== sessionChannel) return;
     try {
       const event: AgentEvent = JSON.parse(message);
       if (event.sessionId === sessionId) {
         callback(event);
       }
```
</details>

<details>
<summary>ЁЯдЦ Prompt for AI Agents</summary>

```
Verify each finding against the current code and only fix it if needed.

In `@lib/agent/services/agent-gateway/src/index.ts` around lines 75 - 80,
Currently each SSE client subscribes to both PUBSUB_CHANNEL and
`${PUBSUB_CHANNEL}:${sessionId}`, causing duplicate events and unnecessary
parsing; change the subscription so per-session SSE clients only subscribe to
the session-specific channel `${PUBSUB_CHANNEL}:${sessionId}` (remove the
subscribe call for PUBSUB_CHANNEL) and adjust the message handler in
subscriber.on('message')/AgentEvent processing so it only processes events for
that session (or drop the sessionId check since the channel is session-scoped)
before calling callback(event) to avoid double delivery to the owning client.
```

</details>

